.SH NAME
pq-genetics \- Population and Quantitative Genetics Tools

.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B pqgen
.RB [ --version ]
.RB [ --help ]
.RI < command >
.RI [ OPTIONS ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
pq-genetics calculates population and quantitative genetic statistics from streams of genomic data. The focus is on speed and ease of use, especially with regard to the input format.

.SH COMMANDS

.TP
.B pqgen div \fR[\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.B Calculate divergence based statistics.

.TP
.B pqgen pnds \fR[\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.B Count the number of silent and replacement substitutions and polymorphisms.

.TP
.B pqgen theta \fR[\fIOPTIONS\fR]

.B Calculate site frequency based statistics.

.SH COMMON OPTIONS

.TP
.B -c \fINUM\fR

.R Column number (1-indexed) giving the chromosome.

.TP
.B -f \fINUM\fR

.R Column number (1-indexed) of the factor over which the stats should be calculated. By default, output per chromosome.

.TP
.B -k \fIRANGE\fR

.R 1-indexed column numbers indicating the columns over which the statistic should be calculated. Columns can be separated by commas, and ranges specified using dashes. For example, -k 2,5-7 would specify columns 2, 5, 6 and 7.

.TP
.B -p \fINUM\fR

.R Column number (1-indexed) giving the 1-indexed reference position.

.SH Author
.PP
Michael Stocks
